<div id="review_989791010" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/989791010" />
    <a title="Kaethe Douglas" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1072582-kaethe-douglas"><img alt="Kaethe Douglas" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1573927565p2/1072582.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/989791010?book_show_action=true">Apr 11, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kaethe Douglas" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kaethe Douglas" href="/user/show/1072582-kaethe-douglas">Kaethe Douglas</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=adventure">adventure</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=feminism">feminism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=dogs">dogs</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=scifi">scifi</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=picture-books">picture-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=friendship">friendship</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=p-o-c">p-o-c</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=animals">animals</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer989791010" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5239172456822672361">2012 February 02<br/><br/>Santa summons a boy to the North Pole in 1908. Art takes his best friend, Spaulding, and reluctantly his younger sister, Esther, with him. Adventure ensues. As Christmas stories go, I quite prefer this to <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/420282.The_Polar_Express' title='The Polar Express by Chris Van Allsburg' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Polar Express with CD</a>. One, I prefer the art direction of Joyce over Allsburg, two, I like the characters better, and three, I prefer this plot, which I kindly will not spoil. Fans of the Pals in Peril series will recognize Art as another Jasper Dash.<br/><br/>Another thing I really l</span>
  <span id="freeText5239172456822672361" style="display:none">2012 February 02<br /><br />Santa summons a boy to the North Pole in 1908. Art takes his best friend, Spaulding, and reluctantly his younger sister, Esther, with him. Adventure ensues. As Christmas stories go, I quite prefer this to <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/420282.The_Polar_Express" title="The Polar Express by Chris Van Allsburg" rel="nofollow noopener">The Polar Express with CD</a>. One, I prefer the art direction of Joyce over Allsburg, two, I like the characters better, and three, I prefer this plot, which I kindly will not spoil. Fans of the Pals in Peril series will recognize Art as another Jasper Dash.<br /><br />Another thing I really like is the author's picture at the back of each of his books. Joyce renders himself with his wife, and later, his children, in a tiny picture that somehow fits the tone of the book. <br /><br />***<br /><br />Ditto to my earlier words. This really is one of my holiday favorites along with <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5326.A_Christmas_Carol" title="A Christmas Carol by Charles Dickens" rel="nofollow noopener">A Christmas Carol</a>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/113946.How_the_Grinch_Stole_Christmas" title="How the Grinch Stole Christmas by Dr. Seuss" rel="nofollow noopener">How the Grinch Stole Christmas</a>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24979.Miracle_and_Other_Christmas_Stories" title="Miracle and Other Christmas Stories by Connie Willis" rel="nofollow noopener">Miracle and Other Christmas Stories</a>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34305.This_Year_It_Will_Be_Different" title="This Year It Will Be Different by Maeve Binchy" rel="nofollow noopener">This Year It Will Be Different</a>, and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/410913.A_Wish_for_Wings_That_Work_An_Opus_Christmas_Story" title="A Wish for Wings That Work An Opus Christmas Story by Berkeley Breathed" rel="nofollow noopener">A Wish for Wings That Work: An Opus Christmas Story</a>.<br /><br />Even after repeated reading, the art is so detailed we notice new aspects. Had I ever spotted the penguins before? And I really love how Esther, ignored for her youth and her sex, really sneaks up on you.<br /><br />Library copy.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5239172456822672361" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


