        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer248945580" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2003153442288567043">It would seem I&apos;ve been living under a rock, because I&apos;m pretty sure this book is my introduction to William Joyce, and it seems he&apos;s a Really Big Deal. (Cue me immediately checking out everything else of his I can find.) This Christmas story has an old-fashioned adventure sensibility, from the rollicking text (which would made a great grade-school or one-on-one readaloud) right down to the dramatic, cinematic illustrations (reminiscent of N.C. Wyeth, Winsor McCay, and Maxfield Parrish). Include</span>
  <span id="freeText2003153442288567043" style="display:none">It would seem I've been living under a rock, because I'm pretty sure this book is my introduction to William Joyce, and it seems he's a Really Big Deal. (Cue me immediately checking out everything else of his I can find.) This Christmas story has an old-fashioned adventure sensibility, from the rollicking text (which would made a great grade-school or one-on-one readaloud) right down to the dramatic, cinematic illustrations (reminiscent of N.C. Wyeth, Winsor McCay, and Maxfield Parrish). Includes an interactive ending, but I won't give it away. This would be a great gift for anyone who loves <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/420282.The_Polar_Express" title="The Polar Express by Chris Van Allsburg" rel="nofollow noopener">The Polar Express</a>.</span>
